data.title: Name Titov: origin, meaning, etymology, and character traits
data.meta_description: Discover the meaning, etymology, and character traits associated with the name Titov. Learn more about the origins of this popular name.
data.text:
The first name "Titov" is of Russian origin. It is derived from the Russian surname "Titov," which means "son of Tit," with "Tit" being a diminutive form of the name "Tikhon." The surname "Titov" was quite common in Russia, and at some point, it began to be used as a first name. It may have also gained popularity due to its association with Soviet cosmonaut Gherman Titov, who was the second human to orbit the Earth and the first to spend more than a day in space.
